hadiths[3]{hadithnumber,text}:
2257,Rasulullah (Sallallahu Alehi w aalehi wasallam) ne har us cheez mein Shufaa ka haq diya tha jo abhi taqseem na hui ho. lekin jab hudood muqarrar ho gain aur rastey badal diye gaey to phir haqe-shuf'a baqi nahi rahtaa.
2258,"mein Sad-bin-abi-Waqas (Raziallahu anhu) ke paas khada tha ke Miswar-bin-Makhrama (Raziallahu anhu) tashrif laey aur apna hath mere kandhey par rakha. itney main Nabi Karim (Sallallahu Alehi w aalehi wasallam) ke ghulam abu-Raafe (Raziallahu anhu) bhi aagey aur farmaya ke aey Sad ! tumharey qabeele mein jo mere 2 ghar hain, unhein tum khareed lo. Sad (Raziallahu anhu) boley ke b-khudaa main to unhein nahi khareedoonga. is par Miswar (Raziallahu anhu) ne farmaya ke nahi ji tumhen khareednaa hoga. Sad (Raziallahu anhu) ne farmaya ke phir main char hazaar se zyada nahi de sakta aur wo bhi qistwaar. abu-Raafe (Raziallahu anhu) ne farmaya ke mujhey panch so Dinar unke mil rahe hain. agar maine Rasulullah (Sallallahu Alehi w aalehi wasallam) ki zaban se ye na suna hota ke padosi apne padaus ka zyada haqdaar hai. to main un gharon ko char hazaar par tumhen hargiz na detaa. jabke mujhey panch so Dinar unke mil rahe hain. chunanche wo donon ghar abu-Raafe (Raziallahu anhu) ne Sad (Raziallahu anhu) ko de diye."
2259,"maine puchha ya Rasulullah! mere 2 padosi hain, main un donon mein se kis ke paas hadiya bhejoon ? Aap (Sallallahu Alehi w aalehi wasallam) ne farmaya ke jiska darwaza tujh se zyada qareeb ho."
